{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"2511789f-213d-490e-a2cc-7884b35f12bf","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, and tasks.md under specrunner/changes/local-provider-readiness-before-side-effects/ on branch change/local-provider-readiness-before-side-effects-8bd5a858.\n\nDesign summary:\n- D1 Placement: a shared readiness gate at the top of CommandRunner.execute() (before prepare()), the single choke point both run (PipelineRunCommand) and resume (ResumeCommand) traverse strictly before any side effect — before run's setupWorkspace worktree/branch/journal seeding and before resume's `running`-transition persist. CLI-only was rejected because run uses runPreflight while resume uses bootstrap (asymmetric).\n- D2 Mechanism: chose a lightweight injectable live probe over \"move the first agent connection before side effects\". Justification: local auth cannot be verified from credential presence (SDK authenticates via Claude interactive stores; existing check is best-effort), and the first agent step (request-review) reads request.md from the worktree, so it structurally depends on the very side effects we must avoid. Probe cost bounded (one call, wall-clock timeout, cheap model, early abort); transient failures classed as unreachable to avoid false auth blame.\n- D3 Seam: assertProviderReadiness optional on RuntimeStrategy / required on RealRuntimeStrategy (mirrors assertNoDuplicateLiveJob); LocalRuntime runs an injected ProviderReadinessProbe (default adapter-backed via createRuntime); ManagedRuntime no-op → managed unchanged.\n- D4 Classification: pure classifier maps 4 kinds (auth-missing/auth-invalid/unreachable/provider-failure) to a SpecRunnerError (PROVIDER_NOT_READY) with prescriptive first sentence + credential-free detail underneath (describeGitFetchFailure shape); PROVIDER_READINESS_HINTS added to hint-command-existence teeth (login is registered; claude setup-token is external).\n- D5 Surfacing: gate prints message+hint and returns exit 1 (not throw) for uniform behavior across run/resume; no RunResultContract JSON on pre-job failure.\n\ntasks.md covers T-01..T-08 with acceptance criteria mapped to request T1–T7 (no-side-effects + mutation sensitivity, 4-kind classification, exactly-once, no-raw-exposure, no real token in CI, managed unchanged, typecheck+test green). No source edits performed (planning only). request.adr === true, so ADR generation is left to adr-gen (no ADR paths written into design/tasks per project rules).</reason>\n</invoke>\n","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-20T10:43:00.474Z","endedAt":"2026-07-20T10:54:00.746Z","commitOid":"c330216ecffe624efa3d89a00c3dea32619c6b40"}
